parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear upper control arm can cause uneven tire wear, vibration, and noise, leading to a loss of vehicle control, accidents, and decreased vehicle safety.

The failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.
